de.esoco.storage

Class QueryList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<T>
        • de.esoco.storage.QueryList<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>

    public class QueryList<T>
extends java.util.AbstractList<T>
    A List implementation that receives it's content from a storage query. The list elements will only be queried when the list is accessed for the first time.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes

        public QueryList()

                 QueryPredicate<T> pChildQuery,

                 QueryList.ElementInitializer<T> rInitializer)
        Creates a new instance.
        Parameters:
        rDefinition - The definition of the storage to query the list elements from
        pChildQuery - The query to read the list elements from
        nSize - The size of the list after querying or -1 if unknown
        rInitializer - The initializer for the queried list elements

        public void query()
